metadata.name: Yellow Boots
metadata.description:
Artist Keri Little 
Title Yellow Boots

Since I started this crazy journey with liquid art, I often see characters on my screen during the editing process. I adore the fact that others in the community are beginning to see their own characters now within my work. I did a shout out asking my community what they saw within this image and my fav response was a man in yellow boots. Although I did also like fireworks and tomato head, Yellow Boots it is.

Welcome to my journey exploring and pushing the genre of Liquid Art. Unlike my first collections, with this collection I am using the technique of utilizing compressed air to push water jet up and then collide with water drops falling from above. The whole process of building this hobby device, and mastering it has driven me crazy over the last few months, but ultimately it has brought so much joy in a time when joy was in high demand. I hope it triggers your imagination and you enjoy a moment just gazing at it's weird texture, stunning colours created with water & acrylic paint, plus it's total randomness.
